From: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 10:12:55 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: intel-gw: Remove unused define

The C preprocessor define 'PCIE_APP_INTX_OFSET' is not used in the sources
and can therefore be deleted.

Signed-off-by: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-intel-gw.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-intel-gw.c b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-intel-gw.c
index 75da3c69ba34..fe919d6bb264 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-intel-gw.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-intel-gw.c
@@ -56,7 +56,6 @@
 #define PCIE_APP_IRN_REQ_RST		BIT(26) /* Link down from EP */
 #define PCIE_APP_IRN_SYS_INT		BIT(28)
 #define PCIE_APP_IRN_SYS_ERR_RC		BIT(29)
-#define PCIE_APP_INTX_OFST		12
 
 #define PCIE_APP_IRN_INT \
 	(PCIE_APP_IRN_AER_REPORT | PCIE_APP_IRN_PME | \
